File libsrc/libgobject/Hashtable.c

This is not really a hash table yet, but it has the interface.

The Hashtable keys can be either strings (char *) or GObjects. The Hashtable values must be GObject's.

For string keys use: 

  Hashtable_put(Hashtable h, const char *key, GObject value)
  Hashtable_get(Hashtable h, const char *key)
  Hashtable_remove(Hashtable h, const char *key)
For GObject keys use: 
  Hashtable_putObj(Hashtable h, GObject key, GObject value)
  Hashtable_getObj(Hashtable h, GObject key)
  Hashtable_removeObj(Hashtable h, GObject key)

String keys and StringObj keys can be used together. For example, Hashtable_put followed by Hashtable_getObj will work if the string representation of the keys are the same. 

  typedef struct
  {
 	GObjectPart	core;
 
 	Vector		keys;
 	Vector		elements;
  } *Hashtable;
